.TH "FILLER" "1" "June 2021" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]filler\f[R] \[en] fill the map as goods you can to block your
opponent and have the maximum space taken for you.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
\&./filler_vm -f path [-i | -p1 path | -p2 path] [-s | -q | -t time]
\f[R]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]filler\f[R] is a game where you bury more pieces than your
opponent.
.PP
Two players are displayed on a board and must place in turn the
centerpiece of the game (provided in the form of a ruby
\[u200B]\[u200B]executable).
.PP
The game stops as soon as nothing has been added to the board.
The winner is the one who controls the most space on the board.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
PlayerA and PlayerB fight on map00.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ ls
  A.filler B.filler filler_vm map00

$ ./filler_vm -f map00 -p1 ./A.filler -p2 B.filler
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Result can be seen in \f[B]filler.trace\f[R]
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ ls
  filler.trace

$ cat filler.trace
  seed = 4242
  A.filler won
  Score:
  42AGAINST24
\f[R]
.fi
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-f \[en]file\f[R]
Use a map file (required)
.TP
\f[B]-p1 \[en]player1\f[R]
Use filler binary as a first player
.TP
\f[B]-p2 \[en]player2\f[R]
Use filler binary as a second player
.TP
\f[B]-s \[en]seed\f[R]
Use the seed number(initialization random)
.TP
\f[B]-i \[en]interactive\f[R]
Interactive mode(default)
.TP
\f[B]-t \[en]time\f[R]
Set time out in second
.TP
\f[B]-q \[en]quiet\f[R]
Quiet mode
